    <h6>Various areas were inspired by/stolen from other places:</h6>
    <p><a class="linkReplaced" identifier="placeInspirations">Spoilers. Click to view.</a></p>
    <ul class="linkReplacer hidden" identifier="placeInspirations">
      <li>
          I straight up put the
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H4dGpz6cnHo">Backrooms</a> in
          this game because I could. Hey, liminal spaces are cool. The
          playground area is a ripoff of liminal playground concepts too,
          including &quot;Level FUN&quot;.
      </li>
      <li>
          The hidden area is heavily inspired by the outskirts of Redacre, from
          The Blackout Club. Specifically the stuff you see towards the
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZEJGw1oWUsI"
            >end of the prologue.</a
          >
          Cool game where the devs could hijack NPCs and talk directly to the
          players, leading to a lot of fun interactions.
      </li>
      <li>
          Greenhouse is kind of a ripoff of
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QHg_gqZ03o8"
            >Greenhouse from Undertale Yellow</a
          >.
      </li>
    </ul>

